{
  "intro": {
    "title": "Word Order",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "Basic order",
        "content": "In English we usually say: **Subject + Verb + Object**\n\n• I like coffee.\n• She reads books.\n• They play football."
      },
      {
        "title": "Questions",
        "content": "In questions we put the verb (or Do/Does/Did) before the subject:\n\n• **Do** you like coffee?\n• **Does** she work here?\n• **Is** he at home?\n• **Where** do you live?"
      },
      {
        "title": "Time and place",
        "content": "We usually put **time** at the end:\n• I go to work **every day**.\n\nWe put **place** after the verb:\n• She lives **in London**."
      }
    ]
  },
